commit.message: fix: typos

change: album art providers can be prioritized with fallbacks

- album art providers return a boolean for success
- providers are processed in list order ('albumart_providers')
- if a provider's name in the list ends with '|' and provides art, the
  rest of the list is skipped
add: support for saving the track 1 pregap when reading from an image
fix: typos
add: saving of the original TOC file when reading from an image
fix: [style] not using constants
fix: unable to start without installed DAE util
feat: show add link when none of the inexact mb releases match
fix: exit code when metadata query fails
fix: reading from disc image files
fix: --save option unable to process empty lines
feat: hide discogs_albumart_token content in --longhelp
fix: exception in --image-file option
use proper requests exceptions
switch from dateparser to dateutil
add --moov-before-mdat to fdkaac commandline
ignore CD stub responses from MusicBrainz
use the iTunes store of the country of the release
update documentation
don't trust the mime property when saving existing album art
display the right release
don't query MusicBrainz if the toc contains data tracks
improve freedb parsing robustness
use quote_plus for freedb queries
remove obsolete support files
reintroduce iTunes album art fetching during freedb/gnudb queries
use requests library for freedb/gnudb queries
check whether genres is set before referring to it
do not strip year if not set
use requests library for MusicBrainz queries
